<subSubSection pageId="67" pageNumber="184" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="67.[151,756,1865,2081]" lastBlockId="67.[794,1399,1353,1537]" pageId="67" pageNumber="184">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,262,1865,1889]" pageId="67" pageNumber="184">Comment</emphasis>
: In the original description, which is based on a unique male from “ 
<collectingRegion box="[388,545,1897,1921]" country="Malaysia" name="Kuala Lumpur" pageId="67" pageNumber="184">Kuala Lumpur</collectingRegion>
”, 
<bibRefCitation author="CAMERON, M." box="[568,756,1897,1921]" pageId="67" pageNumber="184" pagination="89 - 131" refId="ref57714" refString="CAMERON, M. 1950: VI. - New species of Staphylinidae (Col.) from the Malay Peninsula. - The Annals and Magazine of Natural History 26: 89 - 131." type="journal article" year="1950">CAMERON (1950)</bibRefCitation>
stated that this was a “somewhat anomalous species” somewhat resembling “ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dillwyn" authorityYear="1829" box="[415,499,1961,1985]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Astilbus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="67" pageNumber="184" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[415,499,1961,1985]" italics="true" pageId="67" pageNumber="184">Astilbus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” (now a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="LEACH" authorityYear="1819" box="[237,322,1993,2017]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Drusilla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="67" pageNumber="184" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[237,322,1993,2017]" italics="true" pageId="67" pageNumber="184">Drusilla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), but with “the neck much broader”. As can be inferred from his identification label attached to the 
<typeStatus box="[223,319,2057,2081]" pageId="67" pageNumber="184">holotype</typeStatus>
, he had originally planned to assign the species to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dillwyn" authorityYear="1829" box="[900,984,1353,1377]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Astilbus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="67" pageNumber="184" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[900,984,1353,1377]" italics="true" pageId="67" pageNumber="184">Astilbus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but eventually decided to describe it in 
<taxonomicName box="[794,852,1386,1409]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Zyras" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="67" pageNumber="184" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[794,852,1386,1409]" italics="true" pageId="67" pageNumber="184">Zyras</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The external characters suggest that the 
<typeStatus box="[1305,1399,1385,1409]" pageId="67" pageNumber="184">holotype</typeStatus>
belongs to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="LEACH" authorityYear="1819" box="[911,996,1417,1441]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Drusilla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="67" pageNumber="184" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[911,996,1417,1441]" italics="true" pageId="67" pageNumber="184">Drusilla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
rather than to 
<taxonomicName box="[1160,1218,1418,1441]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Zyras" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="67" pageNumber="184" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1160,1218,1418,1441]" italics="true" pageId="67" pageNumber="184">Zyras</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Since the specimen is teneral and in generally poor condition, it was not dissected. Mature specimens are presumably of significantly darker coloration.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
